d in the reflection configuration.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Adding reflection entry and resources**\\n\\nI need to add an entry for org reflection and associated resources, working conditionally with `typeReached`. It seems necessary to have a resource glob for \\\"xerces/xmlParserAPIs/missing-org-xml-sax-security-support-resource.txt.\\\" \\n\\nI'm noticing that the `SecuritySupport` class already has a static initializer for `SecuritySupport12`. Triggering this might cause dynamic issues. I should also ensure that resource access via `getResourceAsStream` is appropriately handled. It seems valuable to decide whether to split tests into separate files and include assertions to verify that our custom class loader is being used, possibly using `assertThat` or `assertEquals`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Using InputStream.readAllBytes**\\n\\nI’m planning to use `InputStream.readAllBytes` from Java 9 in JDK 21. It’s important to handle `InvocationTargetException` because when a method is invoked via reflection, any error that occurs within that method is wrapped in that exception. I need to ensure that for `ClassLoader.getSystemResourceAsStream`, there shouldn't be an error, which makes it straightforward. I should set up the structure to catch and handle these exceptions properly to avoid any runtime issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating native images**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the native images I've compiled include all the test methods. Static analysis indicates that using Class.forName with a constant could allow for proper type registration. It seems likely this is the case. I might need to check if I need to update the build for dynamic coverage since it could be stale. Also, I should verify whether the build was ignored and take a look at the relevant git details.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RlHY11lb8HIYoJAVEdQqcEUi|fc_015711222997be9e0169f8d6b8af64819cb0c409018896ea3f", "name": "bash", "ar